Managed NFS that can be mounted by multiple EC2 instances
at once.

Instances can span across multiple AZs.

Used NFSv4.1.
Only compatible with linux.
Can enable encryption at rest with it.
Scaled automatically.
More expensive than EBS.

Security groups are created to control access to
these EFS resources.

Use Cases
Content Management
Web Servers where you have a simple folder structure.

Performance
Can support thousands of connections.
20 Gbps of throughput for networking requirements.
Can scale to petabytes in size.

    General Purpose
        Web Servers and Content Management Systems
        Max I/O meant for highly parallaized workloads.

    Throughput Modes
        Elastic - when you aren't sure about throughput requirements. Spikey.
        Provisioned - If you already know the performance requirements.
        Bursting - When you want the amount of throughput to scale with amount of storage.

    Storage Class Options
        Standard - High Speed SSDs. Most expensive.
        Infrequent Access - Cost optimized storage. Can be used for lower cost
        and high performance. 
        Archieve - Data is the only access a few times a year. Most cost
        efficient.

    File system types
        Regional - Spread across multiple availability zones.
    
        One zone - Only available on one zone. Useful for non-critcal
        workloads.
    
        Each filesystem type can deliever 11-9s inside of each ones
        respected AZ.

    **You can use lifecycle policies to move storage into different
    storage classes.